        "subtitle": "Traditional Profiles, Complete Coverage",
        "intro_content": "<p>A <strong>Japanese knife set</strong> is the fastest way to equip your kitchen with professional-grade blades that cut cleaner and stay sharp longer. XinZuo Japanese knife sets feature traditional blade profiles like the gyuto, santoku, and nakiri, all forged in Yangjiang with 10Cr15CoMoV high-carbon steel hardened to 60+ HRC. Every set is designed to cover the core cuts you need in any kitchen: a chef knife or gyuto for everyday prep, a santoku or nakiri for vegetables, and a paring knife for detail work. The thinner Japanese geometry means less resistance through ingredients and more precise cuts with less effort. Our <strong>Japanese knife sets</strong> come in both Damascus and stainless finishes, with handle options ranging from ebony to resin, so you can match your <strong>kitchen knives</strong> to your style while getting genuine Japanese cutting performance. Whether you cook at home or professionally, a Japanese knife set delivers the blades serious cooks rely on.</p>",
